WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:02.170
We're free!

3
00:00:02.170 --> 00:00:03.860
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

4
00:00:03.860 --> 00:00:05.710
Bring down Kaido!

5
00:00:05.710 --> 00:00:07.820
Hip, hip, hooray!

6
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:10.410
– Hip, hip, hooray!
– Hip, hip, hooray!

7
00:00:11.880 --> 00:00:12.830
Luffy!

8
00:00:14.060 --> 00:00:15.540
That was reckless...

9
00:00:15.540 --> 00:00:16.490
Hey.

10
00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:21.080
You gonna fight Kaido again?

11
00:00:22.970 --> 00:00:24.550
Wanna join me?

12
00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:28.560
Don't be stupid!

13
00:00:28.560 --> 00:00:32.680
Just look at my partner to see how that'll go.

14
00:00:33.310 --> 00:00:37.390
Be thankful I don't kill you here and now!

15
00:00:39.030 --> 00:00:41.020
I'm done with alliances.

16
00:00:41.790 --> 00:00:44.350
I can't trust anyone anymore.

17
00:00:53.260 --> 00:00:54.620
What's that?!

18
00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:42.560
Let's go, Killer.

19
00:01:44.540 --> 00:01:46.710
We're gonna get our crew back.

20
00:01:48.890 --> 00:01:52.680
It's time we go our own way!

21
00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:11.870
One Piece One Piece

22
00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:12.620
Wano Arc Wano Arc Wano Arc

23
00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:12.620
One Piece

24
00:03:35.450 --> 00:03:40.870
<b>Warriors' Dream</b>

25
00:03:37.110 --> 00:03:39.070
Look what twenty years can do.

26
00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:45.580
Imagine how hard it is to keep
believing some pipe dream.

27
00:03:46.300 --> 00:03:48.830
They couldn't even wait ten years...

28
00:03:48.830 --> 00:03:51.960
They became impatient
and advanced on Onigashima.

29
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:54.170
Everyone died!

30
00:04:02.770 --> 00:04:04.270
What in the world happened?!

31
00:04:08.220 --> 00:04:09.980
It's been ten years already!

32
00:04:11.060 --> 00:04:17.490
<b>Ten
Years
Ago</b>

33
00:04:11.640 --> 00:04:13.800
We're all getting older.

34
00:04:13.800 --> 00:04:17.490
If we wait the full twenty years,
our vigor will only wane.

35
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:21.280
Are we really going to wait
for people who may never return?!

36
00:04:21.770 --> 00:04:25.790
Believe in Lady Toki's words...!
Believe in the retainers!

37
00:04:25.790 --> 00:04:27.790
Kin'emon will return!

38
00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:30.580
Along with Lord Momonosuke!

39
00:04:31.690 --> 00:04:35.170
Since we don't submit to Orochi,
we have nothing to eat.

40
00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:38.800
Disease will kill us before a fight does!

41
00:04:43.110 --> 00:04:45.230
It's Kaido's army!

42
00:04:55.070 --> 00:04:56.760
What're you doing to the well?!

43
00:04:56.760 --> 00:04:58.740
Shut up!

44
00:05:21.430 --> 00:05:24.340
We can't take it anymore, Shutenmaru!

45
00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:27.320
You can't! You'll die like dogs!

46
00:05:27.320 --> 00:05:30.560
You don't stand a chance without
an army under the Kozuki banner!

47
00:05:35.530 --> 00:05:37.820
We can't take it anymore!

48
00:05:40.210 --> 00:05:43.660
At least let us die holding our swords!

49
00:05:43.660 --> 00:05:47.070
If we die, then we do so as samurai!

50
00:05:47.070 --> 00:05:48.580
Please don't stop us!

51
00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:54.290
Do you remember when we were children?

52
00:05:55.810 --> 00:05:58.210
We had a cry to test our mettle.

53
00:05:59.550 --> 00:06:04.390
People place too much value on their
own lives, which turns them into cowards!

54
00:06:12.310 --> 00:06:14.560
SNATCH!

55
00:06:25.420 --> 00:06:28.700
Surrender Names And Thoughts;

56
00:06:29.140 --> 00:06:31.830
Cease Hesitations! Then take the plunge!

57
00:06:31.830 --> 00:06:34.620
That's what our yell meant!

58
00:06:36.670 --> 00:06:39.970
Raise your voices! SNATCH!

59
00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:45.380
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!

60
00:06:45.380 --> 00:06:46.640
Don't do this!

61
00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:21.960
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!

62
00:07:23.030 --> 00:07:26.220
If we die, then we do so as samurai!

63
00:07:48.660 --> 00:08:16.500
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!
– SNATCH! SNATCH! SNATCH!

64
00:08:28.610 --> 00:08:32.490
Why did we need to wait twenty years?

65
00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:35.120
We'll know once it's over!

66
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.250
There must be a reason.

67
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.380
I have no reason to doubt Lord Oden.

68
00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:48.050
Hey! Men!

69
00:08:50.190 --> 00:08:52.140
In eight days,

70
00:08:52.140 --> 00:08:54.810
on the night of the fire festival,

71
00:08:54.810 --> 00:08:58.560
we will raid Onigashima
under the Kozuki banner

72
00:08:59.180 --> 00:09:05.400
to take the pirate Kaido
and the Shogun Orochi's heads!

73
00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:10.290
If you're willing,

74
00:09:10.290 --> 00:09:12.560
follow me!

75
00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:21.420
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

76
00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:27.130
Of course we will, Boss! We've been
waiting a long time for this day!

77
00:09:33.550 --> 00:09:34.430
Ashura!

78
00:09:35.630 --> 00:09:38.060
You guys haven't aged since that day, huh?!

79
00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:44.610
We were once the same age,
but now we're twenty years stronger!

80
00:09:46.270 --> 00:09:47.820
Right, you old dog?!

81
00:09:47.820 --> 00:09:49.720
Yes, indeed!

82
00:09:52.690 --> 00:09:55.830
Silence, old timers! Do not get in our way!

83
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:58.330
Why, you whelp...!

84
00:10:02.450 --> 00:10:07.870
Whoa, cut it out! We won't be able to
break up a fight among the Red Scabbards!

85
00:10:16.910 --> 00:10:22.060
<b>Udon</b>

86
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:18.890
A pirate?!

87
00:10:18.890 --> 00:10:22.060
That straw hat guy is a pirate just like Kaido?!

88
00:10:22.460 --> 00:10:23.930
Yes, but he is different!

89
00:10:23.930 --> 00:10:27.150
He's untrustworthy! He'll betray us for sure!

90
00:10:27.150 --> 00:10:30.770
For crying out loud, why would
you bring a damn pirate?!

91
00:10:30.770 --> 00:10:33.820
Look, the seas are vast,
with all sorts of pirates...

92
00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:38.070
That man is key to defeating Kaido!

93
00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:39.620
Why do we need a pirate?!

94
00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:42.310
Explain yourself!

95
00:10:42.980 --> 00:10:48.250
Oh no, we must have missed something.
Everyone's regained their senses, and yet...

96
00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:52.550
First of all, did you really come
from twenty years in the past?

97
00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:56.180
Raizo, you've always looked old.

98
00:10:56.180 --> 00:10:59.680
How do we know you haven't
just naturally aged twenty years?

99
00:11:00.110 --> 00:11:02.860
Even unintentionally, you insult me!

100
00:11:02.860 --> 00:11:05.140
Where is Sir Straw Hat?

101
00:11:08.160 --> 00:11:12.440
Tama, it's dangerous for you to be here.

102
00:11:12.440 --> 00:11:15.160
Forgive me, Big Bro.

103
00:11:15.160 --> 00:11:17.450
But I'm so glad you're okay!

104
00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:19.050
Yeah...

105
00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:22.240
He's on death's door.

106
00:11:21.740 --> 00:11:22.240
What?!

107
00:11:23.110 --> 00:11:25.050
B-Big Bro, you've gotta be strong!

108
00:11:25.050 --> 00:11:26.330
Don't touch him!

109
00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:30.130
I'll find the antibodies soon enough.

110
00:11:30.650 --> 00:11:33.210
You shouldn't have pretended
that it doesn't hurt!

111
00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:37.500
Painful, isn't it?! Why couldn't you have
considered the consequences?!

112
00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:38.760
Tell me you're sorry!

113
00:11:41.670 --> 00:11:42.920
I'm sorry.

114
00:11:42.920 --> 00:11:44.510
It's painful.

115
00:11:44.510 --> 00:11:45.310
Help me.

116
00:11:45.310 --> 00:11:46.480
Hang on.

117
00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:48.690
We don't need no damn pirates!

118
00:11:48.690 --> 00:11:50.270
Get him out of here!

119
00:11:51.490 --> 00:11:55.350
Luffy, as dumb as you are, you sure are amazing.

120
00:11:55.350 --> 00:11:58.260
I could never do something like that.

121
00:11:59.140 --> 00:12:01.700
Momo, you...

122
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:04.450
are a real idiot...

123
00:12:05.320 --> 00:12:06.620
and a coward...

124
00:12:07.100 --> 00:12:08.500
and a weakling...

125
00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:10.130
and a wimp...

126
00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:13.460
You're just hopeless.

127
00:12:15.080 --> 00:12:16.760
Shut up, you insolent dog!

128
00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:20.140
You have no right to speak to me like that!

129
00:12:21.930 --> 00:12:23.930
Momo, don't hit him!

130
00:12:28.810 --> 00:12:32.560
What are you, a chicken?

131
00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:36.050
I am Kozuki Momonosuke.

132
00:12:36.730 --> 00:12:39.450
The son of Kozuki Oden!

133
00:12:39.450 --> 00:12:42.120
Then get out there, Momo!

134
00:12:44.540 --> 00:12:47.000
Banish the pirate!

135
00:13:01.100 --> 00:13:03.160
Go already!

136
00:13:03.160 --> 00:13:06.060
S-Stop, you fool! Do you intend to kill me?!

137
00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:09.020
Who do you think they're waiting for?

138
00:13:09.020 --> 00:13:12.650
They're waiting for you!

139
00:13:46.590 --> 00:13:48.810
Is that...? Could it be?

140
00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:15.000
Lord Momonosuke!

141
00:14:15.810 --> 00:14:17.800
Thank goodness you're alive!

142
00:14:26.820 --> 00:14:27.810
I see now.

143
00:14:29.370 --> 00:14:31.160
What was missing...

144
00:14:32.530 --> 00:14:33.930
was a dream.

145
00:14:35.260 --> 00:14:38.770
A future... after the war.

146
00:14:39.570 --> 00:14:41.920
It's not me.

147
00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:46.440
Certainly all they are seeing is my father...

148
00:14:46.440 --> 00:14:50.370
the huge shadow cast
by the Kozuki that upheld Wano.

149
00:15:04.850 --> 00:15:07.280
I-I cannot do it...

150
00:15:08.660 --> 00:15:10.350
I cannot!

151
00:15:25.510 --> 00:15:29.600
I want to defeat Kaido!

152
00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:42.340
Momonosuke...

153
00:15:42.340 --> 00:15:44.800
Do not be afraid, Momonosuke...

154
00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:51.600
Do not be afraid, Momonosuke!

155
00:15:57.390 --> 00:15:58.440
Everyone!

156
00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:00.310
Please hear me!

157
00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:06.700
What happened that
fateful day at Oden Castle?

158
00:16:06.700 --> 00:16:11.700
Kin'emon, Raizo, Kanjuro, and I
embarked on a quest for allies.

159
00:16:12.330 --> 00:16:18.580
However, I became separated from them
in a dangerous place with no way out.

160
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:25.710
I could only return here with the aid of Luffy
and his friends, whom we met along the way.

161
00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:29.930
I am still not strong enough...

162
00:16:31.260 --> 00:16:36.640
but I promise to avenge everyone,
no matter the cost!

163
00:16:36.640 --> 00:16:41.650
Even through trying times,
I carried on and never gave in...

164
00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:44.570
for the sake of one wish.

165
00:16:44.570 --> 00:16:50.210
To fulfill that wish, I need like-minded allies...

166
00:16:50.210 --> 00:16:55.440
I need the help of all
like-minded citizens of Wano!

167
00:16:55.930 --> 00:16:59.600
We all share one wish!

168
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:04.050
To take back Wano!

169
00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:08.340
I owe all of you my gratitude,

170
00:17:08.340 --> 00:17:12.890
waiting for us to arrive after two decades!

171
00:17:19.690 --> 00:17:23.020
I am the heir to a daimyo of Wano.

172
00:17:24.800 --> 00:17:27.300
I am Kozuki Momonosuke!

173
00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:29.900
Now is the time to rise up!

174
00:17:33.870 --> 00:17:37.740
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

175
00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:45.210
Lord Momonosuke's courage
sets my heart at ease.

176
00:17:45.210 --> 00:17:51.300
I have an urgent matter to attend to.
I promise to join you all before the battle.

177
00:17:51.300 --> 00:17:53.560
I see. Understood.

178
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:28.300
You bastard...

179
00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:40.420
Is this all of them?

180
00:18:40.420 --> 00:18:43.690
How many are there? It's a damn ninja army.

181
00:18:45.190 --> 00:18:47.130
Are you injured?

182
00:18:47.130 --> 00:18:48.510
I'm fine.

183
00:18:49.650 --> 00:18:52.690
I apologize. I have been a burden.

184
00:18:53.190 --> 00:18:54.700
You have.

185
00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:57.240
But don't worry about it.

186
00:18:57.240 --> 00:19:01.380
If you died, I could never show
my face to Momonosuke again.

187
00:18:57.490 --> 00:19:00.240
<b>Enma
Shrine


Deep in
a Forest</b>

188
00:19:08.120 --> 00:19:10.990
We're heading back to that
house in the snow, right?

189
00:19:10.990 --> 00:19:15.170
As long as I can hide, anywhere is fine.

190
00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:22.600
I want to go back to where
that guy took my sword.

191
00:19:24.240 --> 00:19:28.440
I will gladly show you the way.
Bandit's Bridge in Ringo, correct?

192
00:19:33.100 --> 00:19:35.400
I need my missing sword before the battle...

193
00:19:36.320 --> 00:19:38.540
otherwise my waist won't feel right.

194
00:19:44.580 --> 00:19:47.040
I guess I made Orochi really mad...

195
00:19:47.900 --> 00:19:50.460
It's no wonder our pursuers are relentless.

196
00:19:53.750 --> 00:19:57.180
Otoko... Do you think she'll be okay?

197
00:19:57.180 --> 00:19:59.220
Yasuie!

198
00:20:04.180 --> 00:20:06.180
Daddy!

199
00:20:07.390 --> 00:20:09.940
Daddy!

200
00:20:10.870 --> 00:20:13.240
After such tragedy befell her father...

201
00:20:14.100 --> 00:20:16.400
I am worried I could not be there for her.

202
00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:19.320
I left her with my crew.

203
00:20:19.320 --> 00:20:22.240
She's at least safe from harm.

204
00:20:28.290 --> 00:20:30.300
I'll never forgive Orochi!

205
00:20:32.260 --> 00:20:35.720
I will avenge Tonoyasu,
no matter what it takes.

206
00:20:57.320 --> 00:21:00.290
I would like... nothing more...

207
00:21:01.830 --> 00:21:03.330
than to kill him myself!

208
00:21:16.970 --> 00:21:18.970
You did what?!

209
00:21:20.560 --> 00:21:24.270
You let them get away?!

210
00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:27.060
And the ronin who attacked me?!

211
00:21:28.400 --> 00:21:30.440
I am terribly sorry...

212
00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:33.690
I am disappointed in you guys!

213
00:21:33.690 --> 00:21:37.490
We did capture the man called Trafalgar.

214
00:21:38.870 --> 00:21:41.620
Tra... falgar?

215
00:21:42.290 --> 00:21:43.790
Who the hell is that?!

216
00:21:44.830 --> 00:21:47.460
He is a ringleader alongside Straw Hat.

217
00:21:47.460 --> 00:21:51.420
It means we have captured
the two leaders of the invaders.

218
00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:53.590
Where is he now?!

219
00:21:56.050 --> 00:22:01.300
In the world of pirates,
betrayal never goes out of style!

220
00:22:08.730 --> 00:22:13.150
Even after torturing him,
we can use him in so many ways.

221
00:22:14.820 --> 00:22:17.650
That sounds good.

222
00:22:18.740 --> 00:22:21.780
So, how is the capital?

223
00:22:22.410 --> 00:22:23.830
Please rest assured.

224
00:22:24.580 --> 00:22:27.250
Currently, the city is on high alert,

225
00:22:27.250 --> 00:22:32.630
with samurai and ninja
on patrol throughout the city.

226
00:22:33.250 --> 00:22:35.920
Until we capture all the invaders,

227
00:22:36.510 --> 00:22:40.510
I shall abide no attempt
on your life, Lord Orochi.

228
00:22:44.810 --> 00:22:48.730
If you see any of these people,
report them immediately.

229
00:22:51.560 --> 00:22:54.400
These are all wanted posters?!

230
00:22:54.400 --> 00:23:00.150
Know that any attempt to ignore
or conceal them will bring conspiracy charges!

231
00:23:01.490 --> 00:23:03.070
We're in a bad spot...

232
00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:08.000
We can't go anywhere
near the capital anymore.

233
00:23:08.790 --> 00:23:12.000
Not just the capital! Those posters
are all over the country!

234
00:23:12.670 --> 00:23:16.460
Still, in some respect,
our job is done in the capital.

235
00:23:16.920 --> 00:23:21.180
Our objective was to find all the samurai
with the crescent tattoos.

236
00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:27.430
But all those samurai are...

237
00:23:27.430 --> 00:23:29.770
...behind bars now.

238
00:23:30.640 --> 00:23:33.350
Release us immediately!

239
00:23:35.060 --> 00:23:36.770
Keep quiet!

240
00:23:37.690 --> 00:23:43.280
Tonoyasu's swan song was meant to convince
Orochi that those samurai were innocent.

241
00:23:43.870 --> 00:23:46.700
Indeed, but it is not as simple as that.

242
00:23:47.330 --> 00:23:53.460
The prisoners' quarters are vast. I estimate
about a thousand people were caught.

243
00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.790
Hey, why aren't they releasing these guys?

244
00:23:57.750 --> 00:24:01.380
Do you think Lord Orochi
would own up to a mistake?

245
00:24:01.970 --> 00:24:04.930
He would never admit to his own blunder.

246
00:24:04.930 --> 00:24:06.260
You're right.

247
00:24:06.970 --> 00:24:10.270
But now we know that they're our allies...

248
00:24:10.270 --> 00:24:14.600
We need them! We have to do something!

249
00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:18.230
Law's crew should be in there too.

250
00:24:19.150 --> 00:24:21.900
By the way, Shinobu...
What're they doing down there?

251
00:24:22.610 --> 00:24:25.410
Ah, they're making sky boats.

252
00:24:25.410 --> 00:24:26.370
Sky boats?

253
00:24:26.820 --> 00:24:30.240
It's in preparation for
the upcoming Fire Festival.

254
00:24:30.830 --> 00:24:34.750
Two of their icons just died.
It's hard to believe they'd put on a festival.

255
00:24:34.750 --> 00:24:38.040
Actually, it's just the opposite.

256
00:24:45.680 --> 00:24:50.930
The Flower Capital's Fire Festival
is an occasion to honor the dead.

257
00:24:52.560 --> 00:24:57.360
The more momentous the festivities,
the more our thoughts go out to the departed.

258
00:24:57.360 --> 00:25:01.690
Oh? So this festival is pretty important...

259
00:25:03.940 --> 00:25:08.780
<b>North of
Ebisu Town


Outskirts of
the Flower Capital</b>

260
00:25:14.210 --> 00:25:15.790
I'm glad you're safe!

261
00:25:17.250 --> 00:25:21.550
Yeah, sorry to make you worry...

262
00:25:22.090 --> 00:25:25.470
I heard you all were captured.

263
00:25:25.470 --> 00:25:28.220
We were lucky enough to get away.

264
00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:28.220
Great!

265
00:25:28.220 --> 00:25:30.600
Oh, that's right!

266
00:25:31.390 --> 00:25:33.430
Take a look at this...

267
00:25:33.430 --> 00:25:36.020
Before he died, a daimyo named Yasuie...

268
00:25:36.020 --> 00:25:37.560
What?! Yasuie?!

269
00:25:37.940 --> 00:25:41.900
While in prison, he drew this symbol
and showed it to all the inmates!

270
00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:44.110
Wait a minute...

271
00:25:44.690 --> 00:25:48.070
The snake has two added lines...?

272
00:25:48.070 --> 00:25:49.910
Yeah, that's right!

273
00:25:49.910 --> 00:25:53.830
I guess that changes the meaning of the code.

274
00:25:54.330 --> 00:25:57.710
Those from Wano understood what it meant.

275
00:25:57.710 --> 00:26:00.040
It's Yasuie's final message.

276
00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:02.880
This is vital!

277
00:26:02.880 --> 00:26:05.090
I'll be sure to pass it on to Kin'emon!

278
00:26:05.090 --> 00:26:06.550
Yes, please do!

279
00:26:06.550 --> 00:26:07.970
Okay!

280
00:26:09.640 --> 00:26:11.680
Come to Amigasa Village if you need us.

281
00:26:11.930 --> 00:26:16.270
Okay! Give our regards to the others!

282
00:26:22.730 --> 00:26:24.190
Captain...

283
00:26:34.620 --> 00:26:35.910
Captain!

284
00:26:36.910 --> 00:26:40.210
Your lives are the terms of our exchange.

285
00:26:40.710 --> 00:26:43.880
"Our exchange"? What does that mean?!

286
00:26:44.840 --> 00:26:48.340
Should I refuse, then Trafalgar Law...

287
00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:53.930
will come for my life, thus sacrificing yours.

288
00:26:54.310 --> 00:26:58.560
A threat from a man
unwilling to bet on tomorrow...

289
00:26:59.270 --> 00:27:02.900
is something that raises
concern for my own life.

290
00:27:04.270 --> 00:27:07.070
Captain, we're sorry! We screwed up!

291
00:27:13.320 --> 00:27:16.200
These three lives belong to you!

292
00:27:19.750 --> 00:27:22.170
You're completely free.

293
00:27:22.170 --> 00:27:25.290
Any objections, Trafalgar?

294
00:27:30.260 --> 00:27:31.840
No, you can't!

295
00:27:31.840 --> 00:27:35.050
Don't go! Captain!

296
00:27:35.810 --> 00:27:37.140
Listen, guys.

297
00:27:39.890 --> 00:27:45.230
You can never tell the Straw Hat
or anyone else that I got caught.

298
00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:47.360
What...? Wh-Why not?!

299
00:27:47.860 --> 00:27:49.320
Captain!

300
00:27:54.070 --> 00:27:55.450
Wait!

301
00:27:55.450 --> 00:27:57.740
Captain!

302
00:27:59.040 --> 00:28:01.460
Please don't go!

303
00:28:01.460 --> 00:28:04.580
Captain!

304
00:28:11.260 --> 00:28:12.220
I'm sorry...

305
00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:16.430
Everyone... because we messed up...

306
00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:18.890
Captain is...!

307
00:28:23.390 --> 00:28:25.190
We can't just sit around waiting!

308
00:28:26.060 --> 00:28:28.770
We're the Heart Pirates!

309
00:28:28.770 --> 00:28:31.820
Let's take our captain back!

310
00:28:31.820 --> 00:28:36.660
His life is more important than Kin'emon's plan!

311
00:28:47.380 --> 00:28:49.960
Trafalgar Law!

312
00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:51.420
You bastard...

313
00:28:52.010 --> 00:28:53.840
Leave it at that.

314
00:28:54.880 --> 00:28:58.760
What's wrong? You've been acting strangely.

315
00:28:59.260 --> 00:29:01.720
It's nothing.

316
00:29:04.020 --> 00:29:06.310
Let's make this quick.

317
00:29:07.310 --> 00:29:10.320
Yeah, it's an easy job.

318
00:29:32.920 --> 00:29:35.340
We'll be done as soon as you sing.

319
00:29:37.890 --> 00:29:41.970
Your crew is allied with the Straw Hats.

320
00:29:48.310 --> 00:29:52.780
What could you all possibly
be planning here in Wano?

321
00:29:53.730 --> 00:29:55.820
Tell us everything.
